Position Overview
I serve as a Principal Data Scientist responsible for designing, developing, and deploying artificial intelligence and machine learning systems for clinical natural language processing (NLP). My work transforms free-text clinical queries into structured, standardized medical data that powers downstream healthcare information retrieval systems. This role requires advanced, specialized knowledge of machine learning, large language models (LLMs), biomedical ontologies (UMLS, SNOMED CT), statistical modeling, and cloud-based data engineering, consistent with a specialty occupation requiring at least a bachelor's degree in computer science, data science, or a related field.
Current Projects and Responsibilities
1. Nature Breakdown API — Standardized Output Schema (deployed)
Designed and implemented a standardized, versioned output schema for the team's deployed Nature Breakdown model API, which classifies clinical text into nature categories and sub-natures with associated medical concept identifiers (CUIs) and confidence scores. Replaced prompt-dependent output formatting with Pydantic-based schema enforcement on Google Vertex AI (Gemini), including pre-response schema validation, backward compatibility and versioning, unit testing across varied inputs, and updated technical documentation. Deployed the standardized API to the enterprise AI platform for consumption by downstream engineering teams.
2. Clinical Query Pipeline (end-to-end NLP retrieval pipeline)
Architected and built a production-ready pipeline that converts free-text clinical queries into structured intents, UMLS/SNOMED CT concept identifiers, retrieval signals, and topic groupings. Components include clinical-relevance gating, query expansion, LLM-based intent extraction and contextual environment construction (Gemini on Vertex AI), integration with a CUI extraction service, BigQuery-based concept summarization, and topic formation using hierarchy-, embedding-, and graph-clustering methods. Engineered the system as a class-based service with production lifecycle management for handoff to the API engineering team, with complete documentation, dependency specifications, and IAM/deployment requirements.
3. Medical Concept Enrichment and Clustering
Built a BigQuery-driven cluster builder over UMLS relationship tables (MRCONSO, MRSTY, MRREL) that constructs semantic-type, relation, and cross-semantic concept clusters with deterministic identifiers, producing a per-concept lookup used for concept matching within the pipeline.
4. Clinical Query Context Taxonomy
Defined a versioned nine-context taxonomy classifying clinical queries by intended source of truth (e.g., patient chart data, aggregate/population health metrics), used for query routing and exclusion within the retrieval pipeline, and delivered in structured JSON for programmatic consumption.
5. Batch Processing, Cost, and Performance Engineering
Developed a parallel batch runner processing query datasets from Google Cloud Storage through the pipeline, with automated testing. Performed token-level cost modeling and latency profiling of LLM calls to support production capacity planning and budgeting.
